chapter.article:
1. The Parties shall gradually establish a free trade area, during a transitional period ending at the latest on 1 January 2002, in accordance with the provisions of the present Agreement and in conformity with those of the GATT 1994, in particular Article XXIV of the GATT 1994, and the Agreement Establishing the WTO. 


2. 	The objectives of  present Agreement are: 


(a) 	to promote, through the expansion of mutual trade, the harmonious development of the economic relations between the Parties; 


(b) 	to provide fair conditions of competition for trade between the Parties; 


(c) 	to contribute in this way, by removal of barriers to trade, to the harmonious development and expansion of world trade; 


(d) 	to enhance co-operation between the Parties.
